  "headline": "WebGL",
  "description": "WebGL is a JavaScript API for rendering 2D and 3D graphics in browsers, based on OpenGL ES. WebGL 2.0 (2017) supports GLSL ES 3.00 shaders, multiple render targets, and integer-based texture formats. WebGPU (2023+) is its successor.",
